The federal high court in  Lagos has convicted the former governor of Abia State Senator Orji Uzor Kalu. He was convicted of N7.65billion fraud perpetuated when he was Abia State governor between 1999 and 2007. Kalu was convicted alongside his firm, Slok Nigeria Limited and his former director of finance, Ude Udeogu. Details later.  To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .